        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 17 at 11:02AM EDT by NWS Albany NY</headline>
        <description>At 1102 AM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Forestport, or 10 miles east of Boonville, moving northeast at 55
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Russian Lake, Eighth Lake Campground, Atwell, Wheelertown, West
Canada Lakes, Thendara, First Lake, Inlet, Herkimer Landing, Limekiln
Lake Campground, Caswell Lake, Eagle Bay, McKeever, Northwood, Nicks
Lake Campground, Wolf Lake Landing, Old Forge, Mountain Lodge, North
Wilmurt, and Alger Island Public Campground.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
